AGI - Reclusion from one to five years for those who cause an "unfair damage" using artificial intelligence systems >. Registration to systems like chatbots for under 14 only after consent of parents. A billion euro> appropriation, spread in the three-year period up to 2026, in support of the development of startups in the sector and of at least one company able to assume a dimension of leader in the national market. The Council of Ministers approved the draft law on artificial intelligence to try to put order in a field with very different fields of application - from health to information to culture through safety and defence - whose potential and implications are still all to be explored.
&nbsp;
The document tries to fix poles to the use of AI>, specifies that systems and models of artificial intelligence must be developed and applied in respect of man's autonomy and decision-making power and must not affect the democratic development of institutional and political life. The essential precondition is that cybersecurity must be ensured. For information, the intention is that IA systems are used, read in the draft text, "without prejudice to freedom and pluralism of means of communication, freedom of expression, objectivity, completeness, impartiality and loyalty of information".
&nbsp;
The Minister of Justice Carlo Nordio > has clarified that as to the crimes "for which it is possible to intervene in an insidious way with the AI, an aggravating is expected". The checkers specified: "We try to grasp the opportunity of the IA both in the organization of the offices and in research, without conditioning for the magistrates, nor replacing artificial intelligence to the human one". And again: "Artificial intelligence systems are used exclusively for the organization and simplification of judicial work." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
For the Minister of Enterprise Adolfo Urso>: "The goal is to create a fair, open and usable artificial intelligence market. We must involve the Pmi in the innovative challenging AI process." The owner of Mimit recalled that "the measure directs 1 billion euros of the innovation fund to the venture capital managed by Cdp to facilitate the birth and growth of start-ups operating in the sector. And then to allow the birth of a national sample of the sector, as other countries are doing. They are the first resources then we will see the other needs of the sector".
&nbsp;
Among those who have worked most in the text is the undersecretary of Innovation Alessio Butt>i. "The bill defines unequivocally who elaborates the strategy, or Palazzo Chigi, will be updated every two years and submitted to colleagues of government. We have thought of two authors, Agid and Acn, already equipped with profiles that allow this type of supervision". Butti added: "We thought we didn't adopt the Spanish model the country that before us legislated on the subject. The national strategy aims at particular attention to man, puts together public administrations and private subjects, promotes research, to equip the country with an industrial policy on IA, which today does not exist. Many things will be implemented with secondary standards, Dpcm and regulations."

